.SH "NAME"
idioms \- overview of idiomatic utilities for scripting
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
\fBidioms\fP is a set of useful utilities and functions designed to make scripting more idiomatic.
It\(cqs akin to \f(CRmoreutils\fP, but the main goal is to standardize common tasks, improve code smell, and
also make automating things like safely failing when running commands easier.
.sp
\fBidioms\fP consists of these parts:
.sp
backslash(1)
.RS 4
combine lines that end with a backslash
.RE
.sp
idioms(1)
.RS 4
setup usage of idioms(3) functions in a script
.RE
.sp
idioms(3)
.RS 4
useful functions that work within a script runtime
.RE
.sp
integer(1)
.RS 4
check if all given arguments are positve integers
.RE
.sp
lastarg(1)
.RS 4
print the last argument given
.RE
.sp
match(1)
.RS 4
succeed if all strings match a given pattern
.RE
.sp
ratelimit(1)
.RS 4
limit how often a command can be ran
.RE
